<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>eth·nic·i·ty    P   Pronunciation Key  (th-ns-t)<br>
n.<br>
<br>
Ethnic character, background, or affiliation.<br>
An ethnic group.<br>
an ethnic quality or affiliation resulting from racial or cultural ties; &quot;ethnicity has a strong influence on community status relations&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>na·tion·al·ism    P   Pronunciation Key  (nsh-n-lzm, nshn-)<br>
n.<br>
<br>
Devotion to the interests or culture of one's nation.<br>
The belief that nations will benefit from acting independently rather than collectively, emphasizing national rather than international goals.<br>
Aspirations for national independence in a country under foreign domination.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <p><html>
